snippet: The scene around the strategically important Mosul Dam bore testament to the deadly effect American airstrikes were having on the militants of the Islamic State in Iraq and Syria, or ISIS.
abstract: Iraqi and Kurdish forces retaking the Mosul Dam in Iraq encounter wreckage, craters and other evidence of the deadly effect American airstrikes have had on the militants of the Islamic State in Iraq and Syria; two days of concerted air assaults paved the way for reclamation of strategically important dam, which remains in fine condition.
lead_paragraph: The scene around the strategically important Mosul Dam bore testament to the deadly effect American airstrikes were having on the militants of the Islamic State in Iraq and Syria, or ISIS.
